content.text:
Let me analyze this task systematically:

1. Target Image Analysis:
- Structure has 7 blocks total
- Colors: Green (center), Blue (surrounding sides), Orange (outer sections)
- 2 layers: A central top layer and a wider bottom layer
- Compact, symmetrical design with blue blocks acting as connectors

2. Block Dictionary Selection:
Required blocks:
- Block 2 (Green cube, center top)
- Block 1 & 6 (Blue cubes, side connectors)
- Block 3 & 7 (Orange blocks, outer sections)

3. Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 2 (green cube to center)
    Step2: Move block with index 1 (blue cube to left side)
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (blue cube to right side)
    Step4: Move block with index 3 (orange block to left outer section)
    Step5: Move block with index 7 (orange block to right outer section)
}

The assembly follows a symmetric pattern, creating a balanced, structured design with the green cube at the center, blue cubes connecting the sides, and orange blocks forming the outer sections.
